    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="845"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/610</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SFJ1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-09T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your October 26, 12 noon. Department learns that British Minister has been
                    instructed to notify Argentine Government that his Government will not approve
                    voyage of <hi rend="italic">Bahia Blanca</hi> until an opportunity is afforded
                    them to examine the terms of transfer to Argentine flag. You will support your
                    British colleague’s representations in this matter and will make it quite clear
                    to the Argentine Government that this Government would reserve all its rights as
                    a belligerent should the proposed voyage of the <hi rend="italic">Bahia
                        Blanca</hi> actually <pb facs="0920" n="1754" xml:id="pg_1754"/> take place.
                    Department unable to understand Minister of Foreign Affairs’ statement that
                    since matter has been arranged with <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NRS1"
                        >Naón</persName>, United States Government now makes no objection to
                    proposed voyage, in view of fact that <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NRS1">Naón</persName> has never spoken to
                    Department specifically in regard to <hi rend="italic">Bahia Blanca</hi>. So
                    inform British colleague.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
